The Transformation of Economic and Political System aimed at providing democratic rights and freedoms for the citizens, enforcement of Civil law system with the solution of many issues resolved in the Statutory law in an ideological manner, and having uninterrupted and endurable development of the Mongolia every sphere.
The participation of citizens of Mongolia in affairs of the country and the improvement of living standards depend on the success of renovation in the spheres concerned.
The following represents the most significant and main challenges:
- Social and economic development without any interruptions and the pace of development that matches the time and the requirements of social modernization - Good governance that is performed along with elimination of above average differential in development levels between provinces and settlements and increasing the relative share of the development center - The formation of an ideology under which public responsibility will be factored in alongside responsibility of the state, abiding by the rule of law - Modernization and the development of all types of social institutions that take into account social and economic integrations and sustain the happiness of the citizens
Mongolia is internationally recognized impartiality at the global arena; and Human rights are protected in Mongolia.
The population of Mongolia, which consisted mainly of the people of nomadic lifestyle divided into 330,000 herds, 900,000 cattle, and a total area of over 3,000,000 square kilometers in approximately 25,000 households, all pasturing herds are replaced in separate livestock units.
